pTitle: AmazonBasics Lightweight On-Ear Headphones - Black
rText:
Product came as pictured. They fit just fine. The only problem is the elasticity. These headphones do not stretch well and they squeeze in on your head really tight. I always get a headache after I put these on for 2-3 minutes.

These may be cheap but don't buy them if you have a big head. I am 6 feet tall and these really squeezes the sides of my head together when I wear it. I tried to stretch these out by putting them onto a cardboard box to expand them a little bit. I left it on the cardboard box for weeks and when I wore it again, they fit better. But the problem is they still try to squeeze back to their original shape. Very disappointed.
rTitle: They fit just fine. The only problem is the elasticity

pTitle: Panasonic RP-HJE120-PPK In-Ear Headphone, Black
rText:
Best pair of earbuds you will ever own!
Pros:
~ Better than expensive market brands like Beats.( I prefer them over my $200 ATH-M50's)
~ They are incredibly comfortable, I've accidentally slept with them on several times!
~ The sound balance is great, not too much bass, all audiophiles will love them.
~ They're incredibly durable, I've had mine for a year and they still work.
Cons:
~ They're a tangle nightmare
~ The unboxing is quite underwhelming
rTitle: Best pair of earbuds you will ever own

pTitle: SENSO Bluetooth Headphones, Best Wireless Sports Earphones w/ Mic IPX7 Waterproof HD Stereo Sweatproof Earbuds for Gym Running Workout 8 Hour Battery Noise Cancelling Headsets
rText: I am so disappointed in these. They started out fine but after a short time the bluetooth connection goes in and out so much I finally took them off and pulled out my old wired ones. Specifically any time I go outside. I was hoping to use them while I was gardening or mowing the lawn. I tried them in my shorts pocket. Every time I would kneel down the sound would cut out. I eventually changed to a t-shirt that had a pocket on the chest and put my phone in that. Again it would still go in and out and say "Connected" over and over. Finally I even held the phone against the headphones just to see if that worked. Still I had problems. Inside the house seems fine but they're supposed to have a 30' range. I didn't even get a 3' range. And of course I've had them for about six weeks so it's too late to return them.

pTitle: Vogek On Ear Headphones Lightweight and Foldable Bass Headphones with Volume Control and Microphone
rText: Sometimes, I just gt tired of wearing earbuds, but I still want to be able to listen to music, or use my phone without interfering with anyone else's activities, so I decided to try a pair of headphones. I am very happy with these Vogek Headphones. They are very lightweight, the ear pads are very comfortable and they swivel so you can store the headphones in a totally flat position. The clarity is really remarkable and outside noise is very minimal. I have switched off using these and my earbuds now for a week and I'm pretty sure I like these better than the earbuds. I will probably use these more for my music and maybe the earbuds more when I'm driving, only because the outside noises are so minimized by the earphones I wouldn't want to risk not hearing a noise I need to hear. Great Product!!!

pTitle: Vogek On Ear Headphones Lightweight and Foldable Bass Headphones with Volume Control and Microphone
rText:
First off, I am not sponsored by Vogek, I just needed a new headset and they blew my expectations out of the water.
Now I'm not the biggest fan of on ear headphones, I'd rather use over the ear, but for the price, you can't go wrong with these. The sound these headphones produce blow away my old Turtle Beach Z60s. One cool feature is that the 3.5 mm jack is protected by metal and that's where my turtle beaches failed. The mic quality is also good for the price you pay.
Works with anything that a standard 3.5 mm jack works with, meaning it works with, your phones, computers, laptops, PS4 controller, ect.
Whether you are replacing a headset like I did or need a temp one, this is a must buy.

All in all this is a great set for the money and works very well. Please watch our video review for even greater details.

rText:
Awesome headphones for the price. We play a lot of gaming in this house and with 4 kids its super hard to just tune them out. We have looked at buying a couple of pairs of Turtle Beach headphones to pair with the our XBOX but they are very expensive and their sound is just OK. So we were very happy when we got these and the sound is awesome! The ear pads are comfortable and fit nicely over the ears. Sound range is excellent and bass seems decent. Volume control is done from a switch built into the 3.5mm cable and there is on/off switch for the microphone. The microphone can be folded up if not needed.The headset seems sturdy and looks like it could stand up to some punishment (it has already withstood my destructive 2 year old).

The earpieces light up when the USB is plugged in but with no USB attachment on my controller it was just left hanging. To be honest I stopped even noticing after the first 5 minutes, and then I realized that just having the microphone cable plugged in for power (portable USB charger), it functions (along with a specific button on controller - I showed XBOX upper left button in diagram).

Not sure if they are meant to block out sound or not.... but SOOOO easy to block out pretty much anything but the game! So impressed. I have attached photos with some labels. Really good quality and a low price. 5 stars!

Anyway these rock..... Time for some more Star Wars Battlefront!

rText:
Came in quick with Amazon prime 2 day shipping. I got these for me, but my husband has already stolen them, he loves them so much. I have sensitive ears, so headphones are usually an issue for me, these work wonderfully though! The headphones are large and padded quite well, so they sit over and around my ear, no pressure on my ears at all! My husband said it was the same for him, they fit around his ear, and did not pinch or put any pressure on his ear either. The padding around the head phones and also on top that rests at the top of your head is incredibly plush and thick. Love that! They remain comfortable for long game play times.

The sound quality is good, and the mouth piece also works great, and does not get in the way. While playing Warframe I was able to talk with my friend easily, and clearly.

They also light up! The extra USB connection you get is for making it light up I believe, at least as far as I could tell, that's all it did. The remote connected to the device is for turning the mouth piece on and off, not for controlling the volume of the headphones as I first though. Which is fine, I like controlling the volume form the computer.

All in all, I think for the price, its a really great product!

rText:
Awesome sound and so light. First, I love the sound and comfort of these headsets. I was looking for a set of headphones that weren't the heavy and were over the head type that I could get a good sound response from. I was tired of gaming with bluetooth and these are nice that it has a USB and regular audio cables. It comes with a 1 to 2 converter so I can use it in my laptop that does not have a separate output for the speaker and input for the microphone.

It also needed to not only be comfortable to wear but also have a good microphone pick up. I also like the way they are so light that it is easy to forget you are wearing them. The sound quality is excellent and the microphone pickup works really well. I had been using a Bluetooth headset for the convenience of not being connected to the computer but the little mic hole is not a good pick up and wired headsets sound a lot better. I had no issue connecting it into my laptop and using it. No drivers were needed to be installed on my Windows 10 laptop. I do not have the XBOX-360 but it comes with the ability to hook right into it.

It is also adjustable to fit different size heads. It is also pretty well light weight. IT has a volume control as well built into it. The cushions for the ear cups are also very comfortable. If you want to listen to music and not use the microphone it will fold out of the way.

I would say the Sonolipo Gaming Headset is probably the best headset I have used although most of my experience is with Bluetooth or in the ear headsets. So take that for my experience. But for the price, this does sound great.

If you have found my product review to be helpful, please hit the helpful button. This will make it easier for others to find this review so they may be helped as well. You certainly do not have to, I do not get anything from it, but I get a good feeling that I helped someone. If you have any questions about my experience with this product, please leave me a comment. Thank you for taking the time to read my review.

rText:
My husband is an avid gamer and was always complaining about his previous headset so I thought getting him a new pair would be a great surprise.

It arrived quickly and was well packaged. We found them to be quite stylish. I love the black and red color combo. It's fully adjustable to provide a comfortable fit. The mic is on the left side and easily folds up into the headset so that it doesn't get broken when not in use. Others can hear you clearly without any interruptions or interferance.

The LED lights are a nice addition and work wonderfully when plugged up via USB. This isn't a big selling point for my husband though as he usually plugs it up into his PS4 controller.

My husband really likes this headset and uses it daily. He did mention that he wishes the cord were longer so that he could plug it up via USB and sit on the couch. Our living room is longer so he normally has to pull a chair up closer to the TV or plug them into his controller (which is what he normally does.)

Overall, he really likes this headset and would recommend them to others.

rText:
The Sonlipo Gaming Headset is a pretty decent product.

Out of the box you get two items - the headset and a Y-adapter to allow you to plug the headset into a computer/game controller that has a separate 3.5mm jack for both the mic and headphones.

The cups and the headpad are both made of memory foam and are very comfortable. The mic is fixed on the left ear cup and is semi-retractable. I would prefer that it be 100% retractable, but it gets out of the way enough to not interfere with my vision when I am not on my team speak application. The USB jack powers the accent lights on the headset and they glow a nice red tone which is in line with the rest of the headset coloring.

The headset comes with a somewhat large inline control box that allows you to adjust the headset volume and toggle the mic on and off. The sound was VERY good out of the headset - much louder than my current headset. I had to lower the volume on my computer about 50% and reduce the volume through the inline volume control. The bass was very rich and I had no issues with either the high or low end of the feed that I was getting through the MMO that I'm currently playing.

The main issue I had with the Sonlipo Gaming Headset was that it is too small for my head. The smaller size of the headset coupled with only about 1" of adjustment in the headpiece was about 1/2" too little for me. Although the memory foam is very soft, having it pressed firmly against the top of my head gave me a headache and the ear cups pulled at the bottom of my ears. Although I really liked the headset, I ended up giving it to my daughter because I couldn't wear it. Also it is somewhat narrow, which wasn't an issue for me since I have a thin head, but could be an issue for other people.

Overall the Sonlipo Gaming Headset is a good lower-priced product which I had not technical issues with and produced a very good amount of sound despite its relatively low $20.99 purchase price. As I said, my personal issue with the headset was that it was too small for me so anyone who is tall or has a larger/wider head should be aware of this.

rText:
These headphones are amazingly comfortable! The headphones cover your entire ear, engulfing them with the synthetic leather and cushioning. Any gamer will tell you, headphones that engulf your entire ear are best for game-play. They eliminate ambient noise, provide crisp and clear noise of surroundings, and provide the most comfort for hours of game-play. The ear measurement is on par with most gaming headphones and measures roughly 2 ¼ inches on the inside. If your ears are larger than 2 ¼ inches as my husband’s then this headset will set comfortably on your ears and not engulf them. Either way, they are lightweight and comfortable to wear for extended playtime.

The headphones themselves utilize 3.5mm standard auxiliary jacks for the headphone and microphone function. This means these headphones will work with your mp3 player, cell phone, voice recorder, computer, gaming consoles, tablet, or anything else that has a standard auxiliary jack. These headphones come with a microphone/headphone splitter attachment so it comes with everything you need. No software is required, its simple plug and play design makes it user friendly. The cord is quiet long, measuring roughly 83 inches (including plugs) in length and the mic/headset extension measures 8 inches, so in total length 91-inches. If you are running a desktop gaming system, you want that added length to utilize your plugs and still have length for comfort and movement. The usb plug strictly powers the lights of the headphones. For that “wow factor” while gaming, simply plug in the usb for illumination.

There is a volume control and the mic has an on off switch which I prefer for privacy. The mic pulls down from inside the left ear area giving you the option to have it stored or out for use. The mic is adjustable to 120 degrees up or down and sets back enough so that it does not obstruct vision or interfere with game-play, but close enough to produce clear sounding vocals. If you find that the mic sounds distant or low, simply adjust your main mic settings in your computer.

Sound quality is impressive for this price point; the headset does provide multi-directional surround sound allowing you to hear what direction enemies are coming from. If you are looking for an affordable set of headphones that will not break the bank, these headphones are it. As a former gamer, I bought these headphones for my teenage son who enjoys shooter games and they suit his needs perfectly.

pTitle: Bose SoundLink around-ear wireless headphones II Black
rText:
After owning this product for almost half a year, I must say that I am very disappointed.

To be clear, my primary use case is online PC gaming. It is entirely likely that this is a great headset for audiophiles who are connecting to their phone.

First off, the out-of-box experience is terrible. When I first turned them on, my PC detected two Bose AE2 soundlink devices which were only differentiated by the icon to the left of the device. With no clear instructions, I naively selected the first one(With a TV and iPod in the image). This was apparently the wrong choice as they refused to work at all. After several hours of reading forums and searching for solutions, I found out that I had to un-pair them and select the second option(with the headphone picture) instead. I've attached a screenshot with the two images in case anyone is curious.

After that was resolved, I started up Overwatch to try them out. When I got in-game, Overwatch immediately crashed. After another few hours of searching, I found out that this is a known issue affecting multiple games, and is documented on the Overwatch forums.

It seems that this headset is not capable of producing both HIGH QUALITY audio and receiving microphone input at the same time. For normal voice calls, that doesn't matter, but for gaming, the audio is a key component of the experience.

I was able to play games if I used the headset for EITHER audio OR mic, but I had to have either another set of speakers or another mic for it to work.

Realizing that this was a limitation of Bluetooth, I decided to try wiring my headset to the PC.
Unfortunately, the USB cable is for charging only, the audio cable doesn't work concurrently with Bluetooth, and the audio cable also does not accept mic input.

All-in-all, this headset completely failed at my primary use case, and now I have to go spend $60-$100 on another pair of headphones while these will rot in a drawer somewhere.

rText:
The only thing I have to say bad about the product is that the color of the headphones does not quite match what was pictured. They came in a darker purple, but oh well!

I use these for transcribing and I love how it helps to block out surrounding noise. Sometimes it is really hard to hear the speaker, and being able to focus on just the speaker and not the noises of everyday life is really nice.

The sound is as clear as the audio in which is was recorded on. I used another expensive brand and these are very comparable to them.

I love the cord. It is reinforced so it will not end up fraying as easily as a typical plastic coated one would. It is sturdy enough to stand up to my cats, who seem to think that the nice long cord is for them to play with.

pTitle: Samsung Level U Pro Bluetooth Wireless In-ear Headphones with Microphone and UHQ Audio, Black
rText:
This are prett amazing Bluetooth headphones. Great volume all around for phone calls and audio as well.

One issue I read from a review by Customer got me nervous when it was mentioned that when listening to podcasts or music at the highest volume the sound wasn't loud enough. I initially had this same problem, but I figured what was causing this issue.

The problem is that the Bluetooth has a separate volume control. While it seems like you have the Bluetooth volume on the loudest setting when you higher the volume from your phone and the sound isn't as most headsets when on the highest settings. It actually sounds like it's at the medium to lower settings of most Bluetooth headphones.

This is because you also have to raise the volume on the actually Bluetooth headphones from the buttons on the bluetooth as well. As soon as I did that I had great high quality sound one would expect from a Samsung device. This definitely made my purchase well worth the price I paid of $30 for $100 headphones.
rTitle: Volume has to be controlled from phone and actual Bluetooth as well.

pTitle: Samsung Level U Pro Bluetooth Wireless In-ear Headphones with Microphone and UHQ Audio, Black
rText:
Bought this because of the brand, price and good reviews and very satisfied. I use these for work and working out and it works great for both. Connection does not fail. Audio quality is excellent and you can't find better for the price. Sometimes, if the background noise is loud or if it is windy outside, it can be hard to hear for the person you're talking to - though, I suspect this is most likely due to my low, monotone voice.

I have two iPhones, and its as easy as going to the Bluetooth settings and clicking connect to change between phones effortlessly.

All in all, I think this is the best bang for your buck. I do a lot of research before buying anything and I am glad I made this purchase. #unbiased
rTitle: price and good reviews and very satisfied

pTitle: Samsung Level U Pro Bluetooth Wireless In-ear Headphones with Microphone and UHQ Audio, Black
rText: Works really good and despite that this is the version without active noise cancelling, once that you are listening to music you reduce almost every regular ambient noise (transit, people talking, and those kind of things). The Bluetooth connectivity works good near the source of sound, however it does not have a lot of reach. The battery works as expected for a item of this dimensions, I use them a lot so I always have to charging them at night and then another time in the afternoon. For me the issues with the battery and the bluetooth reach are not a problem, so I'm happy with the overall performance and sound quality of the headphones.

pTitle: BellyBuds Pregnancy Baby Headphones by WavHello | Prenatal Pregnant Baby Bump Sound System |...
rText:
I use the belly buds with and without the adhesive (primarily without). Before pregnancy I always knew I wanted to provide some way to play music for the baby before birth and so the belly buds provide this opportunity.
My little one always hits right where the belly bud is when she like the music. I am careful not to play the music too loud and always use the prenatal setting, which is quite useful.
These buds provide my little one with a glimpse of what the outside world will be like. It provides an opportunity for us to bond through music when I'm not singing :-) I love the included earphone splitter, which enables us both to listen at the same time.

rText: These were a gimmick that I purchased impulsively for my wife. I think she's used them a handful of times, but they aren't exactly the most elegant or comfortable things. Plus, you could just use your phone and by the time you get to 7 months, the kid can hear everything going on outside the belly anyways, so buds aren't really necessary. I wouldn't spend the money on them unless you think you're REALLY going to use them regularly. And if you're not sure, you probably won't...
rTitle: Fine for what they are -- a gimmick impulsive excited parents make the mistake of buying

pTitle: BellyBuds Pregnancy Baby Headphones by WavHello | Prenatal Pregnant Baby Bump Sound System |...
rText: These BellyBuds have been a fun, uplifting component to my pregnancy. I love the VoiceShare/WavHello app that comes with it and the complimentary lullaby album was an extra nice surprise. Sometimes I feel the baby move when I put the buds on and that's exciting. I have not had to use the adhesives because the buds hold just fine under the waistline of my pants. It also comes with a nifty split cord that allows for mom to listen simultaneously (Mom provides her own earbuds, as they do not come in the package.) BellyBuds have provided time to relax and bond with the baby and I love that.
rTitle: Bonding with Baby because of BellyBuds

pDescr:
Color:Orange
Plugfones - Eaplugs with Music


Enjoy Your Music While Working


Plugfones offer hearing protection and music at the same time.

Plugfones Contractor are great for:
Construction
Factory work
Landscaping
Mowing the lawn
Much, much more.
Engineered to help protect your hearing, Plugfones function like traditional earplugs, but with the added benefit of audio. Listen to audiobooks and music while you work with Plugfones. Plugfones are great for those working or recreating in noisy envrironments who want to protect their hearing while having the convenience of listening to music or audio.
Replaceable Tips


Plugfones feature a patented design that allows you to interchange and replace the tips quickly and easily.

Each pair of Plugfones includes 1 pair of silicone tips and 1 pair of foam tips.

We have found our customers have different preferences and even like to switch between tip types, depending on their activity.

If your tips wear out, no problem! Plugfones sells replacement tips. 

Plugfones have been lab tested and offer an NRR rating of 25. 

Next time you go to work or mow the lawn, listen to some music or a book. Enjoy your time with Plugfones!
pTitle: Plugfones Contractor Orange with Silicone and Foam Hearing Protection - New and Improved Line Ear Plug Earbud Headphones

rText: This things are solid, line is nice and long to run to back pocket of jeans. Sound is great, fits well in my ears. Has good bass. Isn't gonna block out a gunshot or anything but it definitely keeps the outside sound down. Used them while running a Weedeater. Have yet to see how they are on a mower. The only thing now is I don't know how long they will last, only had them a day but they are well worth 30, perhaps better sound then apple earpods
rTitle: Works as designed, well worth 30 bucks

pTitle: Plugfones Contractor Orange with Silicone and Foam Hearing Protection - New and Improved Line Ear Plug Earbud Headphones
rText: Build quality is pretty cheap, sound is good enough though. Lots of room for improvement. The cable is thin grippy and round so it loves to tangle up in everything. On a pair of earbuds made for hunting, motorcycle riding, and construction that's not a good thing at all. The earplugs on mine were already torn in the box. Some have said they work great in a full face motorcycle helmet but I've found they stick too far out of the ear with either style of plug resulting in the helmet pulling them out as you put it on even while pulling the helmet apart as you put it on.Probably worth closer to $15 in my opinion. I used to buy JVC marshmallows for $10 at Walmart and they were a little nicer with just as much sound dampening to be honest.

pDescr:
Color:Black
Sound Leadership & Voice Clarity

Featured with CVC6.0 noise cancellation technology, the headphone intelligently filters out background noise for perfect speech transmission in busy and noisy environments. Compared to Bluetooth 4.0, the latest Bluetooth 4.1 technology features faster & stable signal transmission, clearer sound quality and lower power consumption.

Stylish & Versatile Shark Design

With the built-in intelligent magnet design, you can easily trim the earplug cables when you don’t need them and hang the headphone like a necklace around your neck. Prevents troublesome wires from tangling and provides a natural feel through all-day wear.

Easy Button Control

Unlike ordinary Bluetooth earbuds for running and workouts, this comfort-fit earbuds allows for easy and accurate one-touch control located on the neckband, no need to take off the earbuds.

Hands Free Calling

Now you do not have to stop what you are doing at hand to answer a call. The wireless Bluetooth headset allows auto switching between music and calls. You can control all functions of music and calls easily via the buttons on the headset. Enjoy a cheerful chat with your friends while you are doing your office work, housework, gardening, or particularly when you are driving along the fast lane.

Notice:

To protect the earbud cable against the damage of pulling force, please pinch the earplugs instead of the cables when pulling earplugs out of the shark-like magnet which can ganrantee the lifespan of earbuds by using it in the right way.

Warranty

Every Mpow product includes a 45 days money back & 18-month warranty.

pTitle: Mpow Jaws V4.1 Bluetooth Headphones Wireless Neckband Headset Stereo Noise Cancelling Earbuds w/ Mic
rText: Love these headphones. I've had them for a couple of months now and I've only had to charge them once. Granted, I wear them somewhat sparingly, but I'm very surprised that they haven't died on me just given the length of time since I've had them. The sound is very good. I wear them when I'm riding my motorcycle and the earbuds do a fantastic job of drowning out the wind and road noise and keeping the music clear. If you're thinking of going with a competitor, don't. Buy these. I was a little unsure about these at my time of purchase because you often get what you pay for, but that isn't the case here! Great value!

pTitle: Mpow Jaws V4.1 Bluetooth Headphones Wireless Neckband Headset Stereo Noise Cancelling Earbuds w/ Mic
rText: Can't complain with the price of these, but I would rather spend the extra money on performance and style. The quality of the sound was not fantastic but was decent. The neck part would slide to the side leading it to fall off. I really did not like how the wires would hang out and in the way and touch your cheek and twirl, very noticeable. Time to time they will get in the way and has magnetics on the headphones themsselves that would stick to metal objects. I work doing alot of labor activities and these magnets would stick to objects all the time and wires will get wrapped around objects less then the magnet would stick but really not that much, it still does it though, leading the right headphone to stop working in about 5-6 months, like I said for the price, I believe I got my money's worth. What really bothers is the looks in my opinion.
rTitle: Price is good for the style and performance

Inland's foldable Bluetooth headset is custom built for user accessibility and comfort. It also folds into a compact design for easy storage or travel.

Up to 250 hours standby time
pTitle: Foldable Bluetooth Headset, Black

pDescr:
Unlike traditional, circular earbuds, the design of the new Apple Ear Pods is defined by the geometry of the ear. Which makes them more comfortable for more people than any other earbud-style headphone. The speakers inside Apple Ear Pods have been engineered to minimize sound loss and maximize sound output. So you get high-quality audio that's just as impressive as what you'd hear from more expensive headphones. In addition, you can also take calls or control your music with the inline remote. You can control the volume as well as speak free and have your voice picked up by the built in microphone. rText: Mine have great quality of sound and work fine.  The microphone works as well.  Keep in mind that you should buy these well in advance of when you need them because the shipping is slow.  They mail these from china so 18-30 days is not out of the question.  You get two pair in their own little spool case.  I would definitely buy again and recommend these.  I was a little worried about the negative reviews on here but mine are just fine.

I  have several pairs of Apple Earpods, and these are not the same.  Although they come in an Apple Earpod case, and have the same appearance, buttons, functionality,  the plastic on the controls and earpods themselves is different (cheaper, less sturdy).   Hopefully, that won't effect the lifespan of the product.  

Took 2 weeks to ship.

I was looking for some bluetooth headphones that had some really good BASS,BLUETOOTH, and that is CHEAP. The sound quality is outstanding and the bass really surprised me and made me feel happy. The battery lasts about 8 hours and it feels very comfortable on you for about 2 hours or so.

These are defiantly worth the price and the only thing they could of worked on for future products are durability. So it doesn't feel super cheap and the ear cups feel like they will snap off and break.

I WOULD GIVE THESE TO A FRIEND OR A COUSIN OR A DOG OR A STRANGER :DDD these are truly the boss

pTitle: HMDX HX-HP420 Jam Transit Bluetooth Headphones with Microphone
rText: The price it what sells these at Walmart only $49. I had it hooked up to my android phone before I ever got the directions out, it was that easy. Once I got the directions out (they are folded real tight inside the little box with the usb power cord to charge it) then I read what the lights mean, and how to answer the phone, etc. I hit the button on the headphone, and made a voice to text call to check my voice mail, worked great. But you do need the phone to talk into, as I do not think there is a microphone in the headset. The music pauses till you get done on the phone either answering or making a call, then the music resumes. These phones have a awesome bass, I am hard of hearing and wear hearing aids, and they worked great for me. The phone may be a little on the quiet side. but music is plenty loud. Have not played it long enough to know how long the battery plays before it needs charging but the book says charge for 3 hours for 11 hours of party time. The push buttons to control everything are a little flimsy but if you take it easy with it they should last...That's all I got, I am going to go enjoy them now.

pTitle: HMDX HX-HP420 Jam Transit Bluetooth Headphones with Microphone
rText:
I have now owned 3 pair of these in the last 6-8 months. When they stop working Walmart did replace them, yet I now need pair 4! I don't think so ...
Now the pros n cons ...
Pros:
I use them at the gym and find the sound is good, they fit great and block all unwanted noise out. They are loud, if need be and still fairy clear! If someone phones you, changing from music to caller is fast n easy. They work very good in that respect in fact I would rather use them for cell calls all the time if I could.
Cons:
These headphones will not last! Having had 3 pair of this same model I speak from experience. Each time a pair stopped working it was under a different set of circumstances that I will not get into but will say, I never abused them (dropped, got water on, etc.) .
Perhaps other headphones with bluetooth tech of the same price range also stop working when used 15 out of 30 days each month after 1-3 months at the gym? All I do know is each time they worked fine at the gym until I put them on the next time. And for what it is worth they were always 100% charged during each use.

pTitle: HMDX HX-HP420 Jam Transit Bluetooth Headphones with Microphone
rText: I have a wired set of expensive Bose headphones and another well known brand. But I questioned do I need to spend hundreds more for a wireless headphone set. I read the reviews and saw 99% of the reviews saying the same things. Great bass, great over all sound quality comparable to the expensive alternatives, decent build quality and reliable Bluetooth connect. I figured I'd take a risk and buy them. I'm in shock!!! They sound wonderful .... Remember I'm use to Bose wired and other top brands. I can afford these better brands but why if I can get great sound for so much less. All I wanted these for was to listen to some tv when the wife was asleep and not have to wrestle with 15 foot of wire. But I used them to listen to a U2 concert on HBO and sound was wonderful including great bass response. I then realized they would be the perfect answer to listening to music loud and clear in my jet tub which had always been frustrating in the past. They also are great while working out. These really seal out out side noise well and at this price you can take them into some situations you might not want to use a $300 set of headphones. Hooks up quickly to iPhone, iPad and Apple TV. Battery charging is only 3 hours and seems to last around the 11 hours promised. Next spring I'll use them while, riding bike, mowing yard and blowing leaves. Only thing I would wish was better would be longer wireless connect ability beyond 30 feet. But with iPhone in my pocket I can listen any where and have volume and song select forward or backward from the head phones. I'm very pleasantly surprised with these head phones. Price was cheaper online at Walmart and free shipping to store than off the shelf. Highly recommended.
rTitle: Can't Beat These Unless You Have An Extra $200

pTitle: HMDX HX-HP420 Jam Transit Bluetooth Headphones with Microphone
rText:
First off, the price at the actual store was over 10 dollars more than the website. I had to pull it up on my phone and prove it to the cashier before he agreed to sell it at that price.
The headphone material feel cheap, especially the buttons. The headphones are pretty small. Though it was comfortable for the 15 minutes I had it on, I knew that it would not stay comfortable for long. I've had a $25 pair of headphones that actually have cushion at the to so it stays comfortable, with this they don't bother.
The sound quality is slightly below average, my songs sound muddy, almost like I am listening to them on a headset from the 90's.
I will be returning these ASAP and get my moneys worth for the next headphones I purchase.

pTitle: HMDX HX-HP420 Jam Transit Bluetooth Headphones with Microphone
rText:
I've destroyed many different electronics in the past, and let me tell you, these won't last.

Pros:
- VERY LOUD. If you pair these headphones to your phone or tablet, the max volume output is increased by at least 60%. Amazing.
- Easy to pair. Took 0.4 seconds after the very first charge for the headphones to pair to my phone and to start playing music.
- Comfortable. The interior headband is made of a flexible, shock-absorbing rubber composite and they conform to your head shape and stay in place all day.
- Noise-cancelling. This goes back to comfort, but I'll elaborate. Since the headphones fit snugly and securely around your head, the soft ear cups easily block out sound. If you want to go to sleep on a flight or take the edge off the screeching of your crying child, you don't even have to block them out with music. Just put the headphones on and flatten them against your ears!
- Lightweight. For the high-quality equipment in this product, it's not very heavy at all. Works great for people who are on-the-go a lot or older people who would use these for extended periods of time.
- Simple to use. The Play button is king. Start and pause your music, answer a phone call, enter a voice command (depending on the voice command settings on your phone), watch videos that are not safe for work without anyone else being able to hear it, etc. Just great.

Cons:
- Fragile: The adhesive attachments on the control buttons are showing weakness after a month of frequent use. I don't have to tell you that if the buttons detach or become unresponsive, the headphones are useless.
- Extremely vulnerable to water. Sweat, rain, fog, water vapor - from what I've seen, even the TINIEST bit of water makes the rubber composite around the headband start to peel away from the headband itself. I have returned a pair of headphones for this same problem already, but I think it's just an oversight. Inevitable product defect. Not to mention, your warranty is invalidated if the product comes in contact with water. Not for use in tropical climates, wet climates, people with pets, people with accident-prone children, or people who sweat a lot. You've been warned.
- Not collapsable. This just annoyed me. I guess it's just personal preference, but if I have a clutch purse, these headphones are not fitting in there. Make sure you have enough space to cram these when you travel.
- Information booklet is in 8 point type. Unfortunately, if you need large print to learn how to use this product, you will need someone else to help you and read the instructions for you. The booklet is the size of a postage stamp and folded about fifty bajillion times and slipped into the packaging with the charging cord and sound cable. Not cool.

Overall, it was a decent value for my money, but I'll be getting a new pair soon. These just aren't good enough to make me feel content and satisfied with my purchase.

rText: The earphones are just okay.  They appear to be a slightly cheaper version of my original pair that came with my iphone.  My problem was with getting in contact with the company to refund my shipping.  I paid for expedited shipping ($20.19) to receive my items expedited.  I ordered Thursday morning and the website indicated I would receive them on Saturday originally.   The order shipped and I received tracking info with a even better delivery date of Friday however my package did not come on Friday or Saturday.  Walmart said Altatac would need to issue the refund and Altatac said they fulfilled their end and Walmart would need to issue the refund.  I order a lot from Walmart.com and usually don't have any issues but all this to say IF you order from this company  chose the free shipping option and I pray you don't need to speak with their customer service team.

pTitle: Apple Earpods OEM Original Stereo Headphones w/ Inline Control - White MD827LL/A
rText: I bought three of these pairs of headphones. Two of the pairs' volume remote/microphone did not work. This in itself merits a one star rating for these fake knock offs that are falsely labeled as OEM. The reason that these sell for 10 dollars is because they are FAKE! I held one of these fake earbuds in one hand and a pair of genuine OEM earbuds that came with my iPhone. The fake WalMart earbuds in their case are slightly bigger than the genuine ones. I even weighed the two headphones out on a scale and the fake WalMart earbuds weighed a whole gram more than the OEM ones. The inconsistency in size, the volume/mic not working on two of the three of them, and the fact that these are significantly cheaper than the earbuds found in an actual Apple store leads me to conclude that these are fake. One star

I may have spent more money, but quality is of essence when it comes to the sound of my music.
rTitle: Waste of Money - No Base Available

pTitle: Apple Earpods OEM Original Stereo Headphones w/ Inline Control - White MD827LL/A
rText:
I've used these every day for the last 2 weeks. I connect them to my computer at work, my iphone, and my mp3 player at the gym. The volume and pause/play features worked for the first 10 days or so and then gave out--if those don't work, why not just buy any old pair of headphones? Also, they do NOT work with a standard mp3 player. I have a little one with a clip for when I workout, and it's like listening to a CD skip the whole time. It just keeps cutting in and out b/c the connecting plug isn't very good. That being said, it works fine with my computer and iphone--just the pause/play and volume controls don't work.

I'd advise you either buy a cheap pair of earbuds or spend the full amount on real Apple earbuds.

Guys dont buy this item.
it is not genuine and can cause trouble to your eardrum .

pTitle: Apple Earpods OEM Original Stereo Headphones w/ Inline Control - White MD827LL/A
rText:
For the clearance price, these are satisfactory, especially since these days I mostly use them for telephone and other speech purposes. For music, the quality is not nearly as good as the original Apple EarPods I bought approx. 3 years ago. The sound is relatively muddy, bass-heavy, which may be just what you want, but is not to my taste.

This set does have the mic and remote control for answer/end call/start/stop and volume on the right cord like the original, which was one of the main things I was looking for. They fit my ears like the ones from Apple, too. Only the sound quality prevents this from being a 5-star product.
rTitle: Good for phone and speech, not great for music.

Flip the switch and take advantage of proven Noise-Canceling technology, based on the intelligent analysis of environmental ambient noise, and enjoy outstanding noise-free (up to 95 percent) audio performance. The 30mm driver units deliver full, balanced sound for a complete listening experience from 10-22,000Hz. One AAA alkaline battery provides up to 80 hours of continuous, noise-free music playback. Passive mode allows for continued listening in a conventional fashion when the battery runs low. 
Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones:
Noise-cancelling technology for up to 95% less noise
30mm drivers for rich, full frequency response
Up to 80 hours playback from 1 AAA battery
Can be used as standard headphones without battery
High-energy magnets deliver powerful bass and clear treble
Lightweight and comfortable on-ear design
Swivel design for portability
Sony noise-cancelling headphones with 1.2 m tangle-free, Y-type cord
pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText:
I was looking for an inexpensive pair of noise-cancelling headphones that would work decent and I am so glad I found these.  I wasn't expecting much for the price, but I have been pleasantly surprised.  I needed a pair of these to wear while studying because my husband is a loud person who is always making noise and has to have the TV on all the time.  These headphones muffle his noises pretty good.  I also, recently used them while listening to music on a flight and found when I turn on the noise-canceling feature I can hear the music a lot better.

The noise cancelling feature is controlled by a button that can be turned on even if the headphones are not plugged into a device, so the noise cancelling works even if you don't want to plug the headphones into anything.
rTitle: Works Great For My Multiple Uses

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText:
Tried the Bose at an in store demo and they basically 'make the world vanish' when you flip on the noise cancellation.  These aren't quite that good, they just push the outside world back a good bit.  The Bose are just too darned expensive and these aren't so unless price is no object these are a far greater value for normal working folk.  I work near a server rack full of fans and playing music near them is basically a crank it up contest to get over the whirring fans.  These make it possible to play music at a safe volume level and still understand it.  That is a win.

Do be careful with these, or probably any other NC headphones, while they only quieten the fan whir sound, I totally failed to hear the alarm beep one of the servers gave off while wearing these phones.  Some sounds get canceled more than others, perhaps some you might need to hear.
rTitle: Does a good job for the price

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText:
I've owned a pair of these headphones for almost two years and they are the best pair of headphones I've ever had. If you are looking for a good pair of headphones I highly recommend getting these.

Price: These headphones are well worth the price, they have amazing sound, they are very comfortable, and very durable. Thy have the quality of a very expensive pair of headphones, but for a reasonable price.

Comfort: Most headphones I've tried don't fit my head right and usually leave me with a horrible headache, but these are the most comfortable pair of headphones I've ever used. They have the softest ear pads, and the head band is the perfect shape to fit most head types.

Sound: The sound quality of these headphones is amazingly clear and they do a great job of blocking out all outside noise. the sound doesn't sound muffled or fuzzy. its just clear great quality sound.

Durability: I can't tell you how many pairs of headphones I've had that have had one of the speakers stop working, the cord getting pulled out, cracked or broken in the first few weeks of using them, but I've had these headphones for almost two years and they work like the first day I got them. The cord is thick and strong and the ear pads are strong but at the same time soft.

Style: These headphones are very stylish as well. They come in a few different colors. mine are the navy blue color, and go with everything I wear. my favorite part of the way they look is that they're not bulky which is very nice, and they fold up for easy carrying. So if you want to listen to your music with great quality sound, or wear them around your neck as a fashion statement, the Soney zx-series noise cancelling headphones are perfect for you.

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText: I have been shopping around for true noise cancellation (not noise isolation) for a few weeks since the standard bearers, Bose and Beats by Dr Dre are both $300 and up. I have read mixed reviews about these Sony phones but I was at Walmart Sunday and went ahead and bought them knowing I could return them if they did not work. So, once I got home, I unpacked them, installed the AAA battery (included). I went to the computer and pulled up a white noise program and turned it up. I put these on-the-ear (versus over the ear) phones on, which reduced the noise some, then turned them on. There was a split second where nothing happened but then the lower partials of the white noise went away. I took them outside and fired up my air compressor and same thing. So, since I was flying out on business Sunday evening I took them with me. I waited until the plane was in the air and fired them up. The lower partials of the plane roar went away, leaving only mild upper partials. Success! These things delivered true noise cancellation and made the trip must more comfortable for me. A three hour flight and I swear I was not as fatigued as usual. I have good Sony buds that deliver good sound, but I still have to crank them to get over the volume of airplane noise. The sounds quality of these phones is just fine though I would give up sound quality to get the noise cancellation. I am sure the Bose and Beats are better, but since they cost SIX TIMES what these Sony phones cost I think these are worth it and certainly worth a try.

Headphones are pretty good for the price. The noise cancelling is ok. Not on the lines of a Bose set, but considering the price, they are not bad.
The battery compartment door feels a little flimsy but as the battery life is quite long, you will not have to access it too often so its not too much of an issue.
Fit is good, and they are quite comfortable on a long plane ride.
Overall i'd rate these as good 4/5

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText: I have an older model of these headphones that finally began to loose audio quality after close to half a decade of use. While I am still impressed with these headphones at the price I bought them, $25, they have some issues. While sound quality is good and they are quite loud, they are also quite small. Older models would actually cover the whole ear, while these rest on the cartilage. This can become uncomfortable after a while. All in all they are quite good if you can get them at a significant discount. But, at their MSRP of $50 I would not recommend them.
rTitle: Pretty good, but a downgrade from earlier models.

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText: Bought these for gaming and watching TV. There is a very loud ac intake vent in our basement / multimedia room. These headphones block out about 75% of the background sound from the vent when TV is on mute. When TV is turned to a low to moderate volume I am not aware of any sound from the vent. They work much better than my non noise cancelling headphones. Higher pitched / intermittent sounds like voices still come through a little. Works best cancelling a steady him. Overall sound quality is very good. Probably can get a better pair for $200, but for $30 you can't do better.

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText: I bought these in July 2015 for my autistic son to use once he started school. Well by October some components had started falling off and there was crackling in one ear. The last pair of headphones my son had lasted over two years so this was concerning. I contacted Sony directly. They said there was only a 90 day warranty. I explained the situation and they did agreed to an exchange and would send me an email with details. That was Nov 4, 2015 it is now Dec 17, 2015 and after several angry calls to them I finally got the exchange email today. How ridiculous! Suffice it to say I've had to purchase another company's headphones since my son needs them for school and home. And guess what those one are still intact and working great. Very disappointed and will never purchase Sony again. EVER!!!

pTitle: Sony MDRZX110NC ZX-Series Noise-Cancelling Headphones
rText:
I live near an airport and wanted something to block the loud, low throbbing noise of planes taking off. I tried a pair of Bose Quiet Comfort 15 headphones that belong to a friend and was blown away by the cone of silence they create in active noise-cancellation mode, so I know this kind of noise _can_ be blocked with the proper technology. I hoped to find something more reasonable that would do a decent job, and I thought something from Sony would be a good bet.

Unfortunately, these headphones are almost useless in canceling noise. Turning the switch off and on while an airplane is overhead, I could just barely hear a tiny difference--maybe 10%, not the 95% claimed in the description.I'll be returning these.

rText:
I picked up my headphones at the airport on the way out of town. Looking here, I see I was overcharged for them, but I'm making really good use of them at work so I don't mind too much.

The headphones were excellent for cancelling out the noise of my fellow travelers both on the flight up and the drive back home with my family (have you ever listened to a 13 year old and 16 year old sibling pair fight?).

The only thing I'm disappointed in is that my right cover came off and I can't find a place to pick up a new one. I love them, but it's not worth buying a whole new pair to get one part.
